==Resources==
The Chambers of Xeric have various resources which can be used in the raid to make things easier. For healing whilst there are many options in most raids only [[Xeric's aid (+)|Xeric's Aid]] is used, with exception to the bats occasionally gotten from the thieving room.

It is recommended to have at least one person with 90+ [[Herblore]] in a raid, so that each person can have one [[Overload (+)]], one [[Prayer enhance (+)]] and the rest of their inventory filled with [[Xeric's aid (+)]] and [[Revitalisation (+)]]. This allows for highly boosted stats, prayer point regeneration, as well as healing, and prayer and stat restoration. Only one Overload and Prayer enhance is needed in an Olm fight due to the length of their effects. Whilst the prayer restoration is the more important part if Revitalisation potions, they can be used to restore your magic stat quickly should you need to save someone from Olm's fire attacks, as Overloads only reset drained stats every 15 seconds.
Raids can be completed with lower [[Herblore]] levels, due to the amount of Overload (+) dropped by bosses such as Tekton and Mutadile meaning you may not need to make any yourself

Potions may be used in other rooms should they be dropped by previous bosses. A [[Prayer enhance (+)]] can ofset the prayer drain of [[Protect from Melee]] in the crabs room, and make Vespula a lot easier. [[Overload (+)]] can be used in many of the combat rooms to great effect.

[[Chambers_of_Xeric#Storage_units|Storage units]] are built from mallignum root planks, obtained as drops from scavengers. A hammer is required in building storage units, with the dragon warhammer being a suitable substitute. These are important for allowing you to make potions with greater ease, but care should be taken to not overfill them.

